/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:63:The attacker is right that the estimate table can overstate equivalence if it records only headline structure and not the actual losses from localization, projection, commutators, and shell interactions. The attacker is also right that exact rewrites often collapse back to the same quadratic/CZ structure under standard localization, so a step that only permits those rewrites is dangerously close to proving in advance what it is supposed to test.
