/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:5:The attacker is substantially right that the original chain is disciplined but procedurally biased toward an early negative verdict. The original chain's core strength should be preserved: any geometry-first route must eventually control the full stretching mechanism and not just a visually local fragment. But several parts of the chain need tightening before a negative verdict would be trustworthy.
